x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Annals of Nuclear Energy, Vol.17, Issue.12, p.657 (1990)

x4freetext: -THE DIFFERENTIAL CROSS SECTION FOR NEUTRON-PROTON
SCATTERING AT 14.5 MEV.
.SAMES ACCELERATOR OF NPL.
A 150 KEV DEUTERON BEAM OF UP TO 5 MICROAMPS,
COLLIMATED TO 8 MM DIAMETER, WAS DIRECTED ONTO A SOLID
TI-T TARGET, 4 CI, 1 MG/CM2. THE TITANIUM WAS EVAPORA-
TED ON A PURE ALUMINUM BACKING, 0.5 MM THICK AND 4.1
CM DIAMETER. THE TARGET WAS INCLINED 45 DEGREES WITH
RESPECT TO THE BEAM, AND WAS COOLED WITH A JET OF AIR.
THE NEUTRON FLUENCE WAS DETERMINED WITH THE
ASSOCIATED PARTICLE TECHNIQUES, BY DETECTING THE ALPHA
PARTICLES.
A PROTON RECOIL TELESCOPE WAS USED TO DETERMINE
THE N-P SCATTERING CROSS SECTIONS.
. ABSOLUTE MEASUREMENTS
THE ASSOCIATED ALPHA PARTICLES WERE DETECTED
WITH A SILICON DETECTOR, HAVING A 4 MM DIAMETER APER-
TURE, MOUNTED ABOUT 1 M FROM THE TARGET, AND AT AN
ANGLE OF 90 DEGREES WITH RESPECT TO THE BEAM.
IN ADDITION, A LONGCOUNTER, SITUATED AT 5 M
FROM THE TARGET, WAS USED TO MONITOR THE FLUX STABILI-
TY AND TARGET QUALITY.
THE PROTON RECOIL TELESCOPE HAD A
24.322 MG/CM2 CH2 RADIATOR, 1.125 CM IN RADIUS, AND
CONTAINING 2.088E+21 ATOMS OF HYDROGEN/CM2. THE DETEC-
TOR APERTURE HAD A RADIUS OF 0.75015 CM, AND WAS SITU-
ATED 12.666 CM FROM THE RADIATOR. THE DETECTOR SYSTEM
CONSISTED OF PROPORTIONAL COUNTERS AND A SILICON SAND-
WICH DETECTOR. THE PROPORTIONAL COUNTERS WERE OPERATED
WITH A CONTINUOUS FLOW OF 95 PER-CENT AR AND 5 PER-
CENT CO2 GAS AT PRESSURES OF 760 AND 400 TORR FOR THE
0 AND 35 DEGREE MEASUREMENTS. THE SILICON SANDWICH DE-
TECTOR CONSISTED OF TWO FULLY DEPLETED SURFACE BARRIER
DELTA-E DETECTORS, 100 AND 250 MICROMETERS THICK,
WORKING IN COINCIDENCE MODE. THE TELESCOPE WAS POSI-
TIONED NORMAL TO THE TARGET AT A DISTANCE OF ABOUT 20
CM, AND COULD BE ROTATED AROUND A VERTICAL AXIS
THROUGH THE RADIATOR, FOR MEASUREMENTS AT DIFFERENT
ANGLES. 10 MEASUREMENTS WERE MADE AT EACH OF 0 AND
+/- 35 DEGREES SCATTERING ANGLE.
.CORRECTIONS WERE MADE FOR DEAD-TIME LOSSES IN THE AL-
PHA COUNTING, BACKGROUND FROM CARBON IN THE RADIATOR,
TARGET-SCATTERED NEUTRONS, PROTONS SCATTERED IN THE
PRT APERTURE, PROTON REACTIONS IN SILICON, AND DEAD-
TIME IN THE PRT ELECTRONICS. THE CALCULATED PRT EFFI-
CIENCY WAS CONSIDERED TO BE EXACT.
THE 180 DEGREE CROSS SECTION AND
THE 110/180 DEGREE CROSS SECTION RATIO HAS
THE ERRORS CONTRIBUTIONS GIVEN IN PROPER SUBENTS
.DATA OBTAINED FROM MAIN REF.
N.O.
+ + ENTRY CORRECTED BY S. MAEV
INCIDENT NEUTRON ENERGY PUT IN SAN 001
